$$
\begin{array}{l}
5 \times\left(1+\frac{1}{5}\right), \\
=5 \times \frac{6}{5}, \\
=6 \text { (hours); }
\end{array}
$$

The entire distance is:
$$
\begin{array}{l}
40 \div\left[1-\left(\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{6}\right) \times 2\right], \\
=40 \div\left[1-\frac{11}{15}\right], \\
=40 \div \frac{4}{15}, \\
=40 \times \frac{15}{4}, \\
=150 \text { (km); }
\end{array}
$$

Answer: The distance between locations A and B is 150 km.
